{"id":39882,"date":"2023-04-22T17:23:45","date_gmt":"2023-04-22T13:23:45","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=39882"},"modified":"2023-04-22T17:23:45","modified_gmt":"2023-04-22T13:23:45","slug":"shahada-absolves-idolatry","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/04\/22\/shahada-absolves-idolatry\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Shirk: Word of faith absolves from idolatry"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Salam reported: We were travelling with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, when people were heard saying, \u201cWhich deeds are best, O Messenger of Allah?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Faith in Allah and His Messenger, jihad in the way of Allah, and a righteous Hajj pilgrimage.<\/strong>\u201d Then, a caller was heard in the valley, \u201cI bear witness there is no God but Allah and Muhammad is the Messenger of Allah!\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>I bear witness as well! I testify that no one bears witness to it but that he is innocent of idolatry.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 23783<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih li ghayrihi<\/em><\/strong> (authentic due to external evidence) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0646\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0646\u064e\u0633\u0650\u064a\u0631\u064f \u0645\u064e\u0639\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0630\u0652 \u0633\u064e\u0645\u0650\u0639\u064e \u0627\u